  "lastReviewFeedback": "coderabbitai: **Actionable comments posted: 8**\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for all review comments with AI agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nInline comments:\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-accordion/hx-accordion-item.styles.ts`:\n- Around line 9-11: The stylesheet is using literal fallback values instead of\ntoken-only cascades; update the hx-accordion-item styles to remove hardcoded\nfallbacks (e.g., replace occurrences like var(--hx-accordion-border-color,\n`#dee2e6`) and var(--hx-font-family-sans, sans-serif) with token-only var(...)\nusages) and remove numeric literals in properties (border-width, spacing,\ndurations, font-size, line-height) so every value solely consumes a design token\n(e.g., use --hx-border-width-thin, --hx-accordion-border-color, --hx-font-size,\n--hx-spacing-*, --hx-transition-duration-* tokens directly). Locate and fix all\ninstances in this module where literals appear (including the\nborder-bottom/font-family line and the other ranges called out) so no hardcoded\ncolors, spacing, typography, or timing remain and each var(...) has no literal\nfallback.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-accordion/hx-accordion-item.ts`:\n- Around line 135-153: The region element with role=\"region\" is unlabeled; give\nit an accessible name by adding an id on the summary trigger and referencing\nthat id from the region via aria-labelledby. Update the template where <summary\npart=\"trigger\" ...> is rendered (the trigger/summary element used with\n_handleSummaryClick/_handleKeyDown) to include a stable id (e.g., compute or use\na component-scoped id like this._summaryId or this.id + '-summary'), and set\naria-labelledby=\"${thatId}\" on the inner div with role=\"region\" (the element\nwith part=\"content\" / class=\"content\") so screen readers announce the summary as\nthe region label.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-accordion/hx-accordion.stories.ts`:\n- Line 144: Replace each fixed \"await ne",
